sentences.english: Only few States continue to maintain a separate chancery court.
sentences.chinese: 只有少数几个州继续保持独立的衡平法院。

sentences.chinese: 从山顶我们可以眺三个州。

sentences.english: It also covers in detail state appellate decisions construing the policy provisions.

sentences.english: This achievement led to the establishment of what was to become the renowned Connecticut clock-making industry.
sentences.chinese: 这项成就为康乃狄克州打造出名声卓越的钟表工业。

sentences.english: By 1916, more than half the states held presidential primaries.

sentences.english: Maine is the only state that has a one-syllable name.

sentences.english: By 1936, only a dozen states continued to hold presidential primaries.

sentences.english: The Education Department said coaching was 'a private matter for parents'.

sentences.english: Wooing the Granite State is fiendishly hard.
sentences.chinese: 要赢得“花岗岩州”有如过刀山下火海。

sentences.english: It was admitted as the 21st state in 1818.

sentences.english: The grand jury has been abolished in England and in approximately one-half of the states in the U. S.
sentences.chinese: 大陪审团在英国以及美国大部分州已经被废除了。
